************************
Installing web server on EC2
************************

*  Start an EC2 instance

* In security group select ssh and http

* Connect to server

* Take control

* Update the server
# sudo apt-get update

* Install apache web server
# sudo apt-get install apache2

* Verify whether service started or not
# sudo service apache2 status
* If service not stated then start it
# sudo service apache2 start

* Go to browser and enter the public IP
* you get Apache2 Ubuntu Default Page

* If you want to change that page
* Switch to root user
# sudo su

* Change directory to /var/www/html
# cd /var/www/html

* Edit index.html
# nano index.html
* write script or text that you want to be as a default page.

* exit from root
# exit

* Go to browser and enter the public IP
* you get your edited default page.



